The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 9: The government is considering selling a 10 per cent stake in Neyveli Lignite Corporation, minister of state Dasari Narayan Rao informed the Rajya Sabha in a written reply today. He said the final decision was yet to be taken. The government holds a 93.56 per cent stake in the company. Based on Neyveli?s stock price on the bourses, the government can raise Rs 134.2 crore by selling 1.67 crore shares in the company.

 Mumbai, March 9: VIP Industries Ltd today formed a committee of directors to evaluate the proposed merger of Blowplast Ltd with itself. The panel was constituted at a meeting of the board of directors, VIP told stock exchanges.

 New Delhi, March 9: In a major relief to Reliance group firm IPCL, the government has ruled that state-run gas firm GAIL (India) Ltd cannot charge marketing margin on supply of natural gas.

 Mumbai, March 9: The BSE benchmark 30-share index today made a strong comeback, rebounding from the day?s low of 10376.54 to end 65 points up at 10573.54.

 London, March 9: Belgium will decide on Lakshmi Mittal?s $22.1-billion hostile bid for Arcelor next month, said Guy Verhofstadt, the country?s Prime Minister.




